Richard A Guay <rag@asicint.com> writes:

> I just joined this list and would like to know the answer to a
> perplexing problem.  Anytime I set a user to using zsh as their
> default shell, they can not ftp into that account.

Presumably you have not listed zsh in /etc/shells.  If your login
shell isn't listed in that file ftpd refuses the connection.  Check
the man pages on /etc/shells and on ftpd.

Hope this helps.

Bas.


